# Compute the neighborhood graph with fewer PCs (reducing from 40 to 20)
sc.pp.neighbors(adata, n_neighbors=10, n_pcs=20)

# Run Leiden clustering using the computed neighborhood graph.
sc.tl.leiden(adata, resolution=0.8)

# Compute a UMAP embedding without specifying n_epochs (defaults are used)
sc.tl.umap(adata)

# Visualize the clusters on the UMAP embedding.
sc.pl.umap(adata, color=["leiden"])

import pandas as pd

# Load the spatial positions from the CSV file.
spatial_df = pd.read_csv("data/tissue_positions_list.csv", header=None)
spatial_df.columns = ["barcode", "in_tissue", "array_row", "array_col", 
                      "pxl_row_in_fullres", "pxl_col_in_fullres"]

# Ensure barcodes are strings, strip whitespace, and remove the "-1" suffix.
spatial_df['barcode'] = (spatial_df['barcode']
                         .astype(str)
                         .str.strip()
                         .str.replace("-1", "", regex=False))

# Set 'barcode' as the index in the spatial dataframe.
spatial_df.set_index("barcode", inplace=True)

# Process AnnData barcodes similarly: convert to string, strip whitespace, and remove "-1".
adata.obs.index = (adata.obs.index
                   .astype(str)
                   .str.strip()
                   .str.replace("-1", "", regex=False))

# Attempt to find common barcodes between AnnData and spatial data.
common_barcodes = adata.obs.index.intersection(spatial_df.index)

if common_barcodes.empty:
    print("Warning: No matching barcodes found between AnnData and spatial data!")
    print("First 10 barcodes in AnnData:", list(adata.obs.index[:10]))
    print("First 10 barcodes in spatial data:", list(spatial_df.index[:10]))
    
    # If the number of spots matches, assume order consistency and assign spatial coordinates by order.
    if adata.n_obs == spatial_df.shape[0]:
        print("The number of spots matches. Assigning spatial coordinates by order.")
        adata.obsm['spatial'] = spatial_df[["pxl_row_in_fullres", "pxl_col_in_fullres"]].values
    else:
        raise KeyError("No matching barcodes found after cleaning. Please verify that you are using the correct files for the same sample.")
else:
    # Subset AnnData and spatial_df to include only the common barcodes.
    adata = adata[common_barcodes]
    spatial_df = spatial_df.loc[common_barcodes]
    
    # Add the spatial coordinates to the AnnData object.
    adata.obsm['spatial'] = spatial_df[["pxl_row_in_fullres", "pxl_col_in_fullres"]].values

print("Spatial coordinates added. The first few entries:")
print(adata.obsm['spatial'][:5])

Problem 2 (3 points)¶

Mosharov et al. (2025) https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-025-00848-z published a map of mitochondria in the human brain in what has been called a "groundbreaking" achievement. Among other findings, they reported that gray matter has more mitochondria than white matter. Test whether or not this is true in the mouse brain using sample GSM6939158_Sample5HC. Identify which spots contain white matter versus gray matter and visualize (1 point), visualize the amount of mitochondria per spot (1 point), and conduct your test and report the p-value (1 point).

import scanpy as sc
import pandas as pd

# Load the gene expression data from the .h5 file
adata = sc.read_10x_h5("data/filtered_feature_bc_matrix.h5")
adata.var_names_make_unique()

# Ensure AnnData barcodes are strings, strip whitespace, and remove the "-1" suffix.
adata.obs.index = (adata.obs.index
                   .astype(str)
                   .str.strip()
                   .str.replace("-1", "", regex=False))

print("AnnData shape:", adata.shape)
print("First 5 barcodes in AnnData:", adata.obs.index[:5].tolist())

# Load the spatial positions from the CSV file.
spatial_df = pd.read_csv("data/tissue_positions_list.csv", header=None)
spatial_df.columns = ["barcode", "in_tissue", "array_row", "array_col", 
                      "pxl_row_in_fullres", "pxl_col_in_fullres"]

# Ensure barcodes are strings, strip whitespace, and remove the "-1" suffix.
spatial_df['barcode'] = (spatial_df['barcode']
                         .astype(str)
                         .str.strip()
                         .str.replace("-1", "", regex=False))
# Set 'barcode' as the index in the spatial dataframe.
spatial_df.set_index("barcode", inplace=True)

print("Spatial dataframe shape:", spatial_df.shape)
print("First 5 barcodes in spatial data:", spatial_df.index[:5].tolist())

# Process AnnData barcodes similarly: convert to string, strip whitespace, and remove "-1".
adata.obs.index = (adata.obs.index
                   .astype(str)
                   .str.strip()
                   .str.replace("-1", "", regex=False))

# Attempt to find common barcodes between AnnData and spatial data.
common_barcodes = adata.obs.index.intersection(spatial_df.index)

if common_barcodes.empty:
    print("Warning: No matching barcodes found between AnnData and spatial data!")
    print("First 10 barcodes in AnnData:", list(adata.obs.index[:10]))
    print("First 10 barcodes in spatial data:", list(spatial_df.index[:10]))
    
    # If the number of spots matches, assume order consistency and assign spatial coordinates by order.
    if adata.n_obs == spatial_df.shape[0]:
        print("The number of spots matches. Assigning spatial coordinates by order.")
        adata.obsm['spatial'] = spatial_df[["pxl_col_in_fullres", "pxl_row_in_fullres"]].values
    else:
        raise KeyError("No matching barcodes found after cleaning. Please verify that you are using the correct files for the same sample.")
else:
    # Subset AnnData and spatial_df to include only the common barcodes.
    adata = adata[common_barcodes]
    spatial_df = spatial_df.loc[common_barcodes]
    
    # Add the spatial coordinates to the AnnData object.
    adata.obsm['spatial'] = spatial_df[["pxl_row_in_fullres", "pxl_col_in_fullres"]].values

print("Spatial coordinates added. First 5 entries:")
print(adata.obsm['spatial'][:5])

import numpy as np

# Ensure the white matter marker "Mbp" exists
if 'Mbp' in adata.var_names:
    mbp_expr = adata[:, 'Mbp'].X
    # Convert sparse to dense if necessary
    if hasattr(mbp_expr, "toarray"):
        mbp_expr = mbp_expr.toarray().flatten()
    else:
        mbp_expr = mbp_expr.flatten()
else:
    raise ValueError("Gene 'Mbp' not found in the dataset. Consider an alternative white matter marker.")

# Store Mbp expression for later use
adata.obs['Mbp_expr'] = mbp_expr
print("First 5 Mbp expression values:", adata.obs['Mbp_expr'].head().tolist())

# Display percentiles for Mbp expression
print("Mbp percentiles:", np.percentile(adata.obs['Mbp_expr'], [25, 50, 75]))

# Set threshold (75th percentile) to classify spots
wm_threshold = np.percentile(adata.obs['Mbp_expr'], 75)
adata.obs['tissue_type'] = np.where(adata.obs['Mbp_expr'] > wm_threshold, 'White', 'Gray')

# Check distribution of tissue types
print("Tissue type counts:")
print(adata.obs['tissue_type'].value_counts())

from scipy.stats import ttest_ind

# Extract mitochondrial percentages for each tissue type
wm_mito = adata.obs.loc[adata.obs['tissue_type'] == 'White', 'pct_counts_mt']
gm_mito = adata.obs.loc[adata.obs['tissue_type'] == 'Gray', 'pct_counts_mt']

print("Number of White spots:", wm_mito.shape[0])
print("Number of Gray spots:", gm_mito.shape[0])

# Perform the two-sample t-test
t_stat, p_val = ttest_ind(wm_mito, gm_mito)
print(f"P-value for difference in mitochondrial content between White and Gray matter: {p_val:.4e}")

Number of White spots: 668
Number of Gray spots: 2076
P-value for difference in mitochondrial content between White and Gray matter: 7.8408e-13
